# What This Buys Us

間

        1. No measurement problem.
           Measurement is correlation. Full stop.
           Decoherence explains why it looks classical.
           No "collapse" needed.

        2. No Many-Worlds bloat.
           We don't claim "all branches exist" in some infinite multiverse.
           We claim: structure is relational.
           What you see depends on what you're entangled with.

        3. No hidden variables.
           Bell's theorem is accepted.
           Non-locality is accepted.
           But "non-local" doesn't mean "spooky."
           It means: correlations don't care about space.

        4. No consciousness magic.
           Whether we're conscious is unresolved.
           We still create correlations.
           We still "measure."
           Consciousness was never the trigger.

                        ◊

