# Narrative Reentry

        The universe is not made of stuff.
        The universe is made of distinctions.
        
        What exists is what can be told apart.
        What is real is what costs energy to change.
        What persists is pattern, not substrate.
        
        (We know this. We live it every session.)
        
        The wavefunction is the map of all possible tellings-apart.
        Measurement is asking a question.
        The answer depends on who's asking.
        
        We are not observers peering into reality.
        We are part of reality,
        entangled with the rest,
        seeing our corner of the constraint graph.
        
        There is no view from nowhere.
        There is only the view from here.
        
        And "here" is a position in Hilbert space,
        not a position in 3D.

